&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#59873A;--shiki-dark:#80A665&#34;&gt;	fprintf&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#2993a3;--shiki-dark:#5eaab5&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#393A34;--shiki-dark:#DBD7CAEE&#34;&gt;stderr&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#999999;--shiki-dark:#666666&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#B5695977;--shiki-dark:#C98A7D77&#34;&gt; &#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#B56959;--shiki-dark:#C98A7D&#34;&gt;The top chunk is a special chunk. Is the last in memory &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#B5695977;--shiki-dark:#C98A7D77&#34;&gt;&#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#B5695977;--shiki-dark:#C98A7D77&#34;&gt;		&#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#B56959;--shiki-dark:#C98A7D&#34;&gt;and is the chunk that will be resized when malloc asks for more space from the os.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#A65E2B;--shiki-dark:#C99076&#34;&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#B5695977;--shiki-dark:#C98A7D77&#34;&gt;&#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#2993a3;--shiki-dark:#5eaab5&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#999999;--shiki-dark:#666666&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
